Note:
Runa Standard Library: Advanced String Encoding and Unicode Processing

Production-grade text encoding, decoding, and Unicode handling system designed
to surpass competitors like Python's codecs, Java's Charset, C#'s Encoding,
and Go's unicode packages. Comprehensive support for all major encodings.

Key Features:
- Complete UTF-8, UTF-16, UTF-32 encoding/decoding with BOM handling
- ASCII, Latin-1, CP1252, and legacy encoding support
- Base64, Base32, Hex, URL encoding with standard and custom alphabets
- Unicode normalization (NFC, NFD, NFKC, NFKD) and case folding
- Character set detection and validation
- Efficient byte-string conversions with error handling strategies
- Punycode encoding for internationalized domain names
- Advanced escape sequence processing (HTML, JSON, XML, C-style)
- Stream-based encoding for large data processing
- AI/agent-friendly interfaces with comprehensive metadata

Architecture:
Built on Runa's natural language primitives with optimized lookup tables
and bit manipulation for maximum performance. Uses state machines for
complex encoding protocols and provides both high-level and low-level APIs.
:End Note

Import "string/format" as Format

Note: Core Encoding Types and Constants
Type called "EncodingResult":
    success as Boolean
    data as String
    bytes_processed as Integer
    error_message as String
    encoding_used as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "DecodingResult":
    success as Boolean
    text as String
    bytes_consumed as Integer
    error_message as String
    detected_encoding as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "EncodingOptions":
    encoding_name as String
    error_handling as String
    include_bom as Boolean
    strict_validation as Boolean
    custom_alphabet as Optional[String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "UnicodeNormalization":
    form as String
    composed as Boolean
    compatible as Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "CharacterSetInfo":
    name as String
    aliases as List[String]
    description as String
    is_ascii_compatible as Boolean
    supports_unicode as Boolean
    byte_order_marks as List[String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Encoding Detection and Validation
Process called "detect_encoding" that takes data as String returns String:
    Note: Detect text encoding from byte patterns and BOMs
    If length of data is less than 3:
    Return "ascii" Note: Check for Byte Order Marks (BOMs)
    Let first_bytes be Format.substring with s as data and start as 0 and end as 3 If starts_with_bom with data as data and bom as utf8_bom:
    Return "utf-8"
    Otherwise if starts_with_bom with data as data and bom as utf16_be_bom:
    Return "utf-16-be"
    Otherwise if starts_with_bom with data as data and bom as utf16_le_bom:
    Return "utf-16-le"
    Otherwise if length of data is greater than or equal to 4 and starts_with_bom with data as data and bom as utf32_be_bom:
    Return "utf-32-be"
    Otherwise if length of data is greater than or equal to 4 and starts_with_bom with data as data and bom as utf32_le_bom:
    Return "utf-32-le" Note: Statistical analysis for encoding detection
    Let ascii_score be calculate_ascii_score with data as data
    Let utf8_score be calculate_utf8_score with data as data
    Let latin1_score be calculate_latin1_score with data as data If ascii_score is greater than or equal to 0.95:
    Return "ascii"
    Otherwise if utf8_score is greater than or equal to 0.90:
    Return "utf-8"
    Otherwise if latin1_score is greater than or equal to 0.80:
    Return "latin-1"
    Otherwise:
    Return "utf-8" Note: Default fallback

Process called "validate_encoding" that takes text as String and encoding as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Validate that text conforms to specified encoding
    Match encoding:
    When "ascii":
    Return validate_ascii with text as text
    When "utf-8":
    Return validate_utf8 with text as text
    When "latin-1":
    Return validate_latin1 with text as text
    When "utf-16":
    Return validate_utf16 with text as text
    When "utf-32":
    Return validate_utf32 with text as text
    Otherwise:
    Return false

Process called "get_encoding_info" that takes encoding_name as String returns CharacterSetInfo:
    Note: Get comprehensive information about encoding
    Match encoding_name:
    When "utf-8":
    Return CharacterSetInfo with:
    name as "UTF-8"
    aliases as list containing "utf8", "u8"
    description as "Unicode Transformation Format - 8-bit"
    is_ascii_compatible as true
    supports_unicode as true
    byte_order_marks as list containing "\xEF\xBB\xBF"
    metadata as dictionary containing
    When "ascii":
    Return CharacterSetInfo with:
    name as "ASCII"
    aliases as list containing "us-ascii", "ansi_x3.4-1968"
    description as "American Standard Code for Information Interchange"
    is_ascii_compatible as true
    supports_unicode as false
    byte_order_marks as list containing
    metadata as dictionary containing
    When "latin-1":
    Return CharacterSetInfo with:
    name as "ISO-8859-1"
    aliases as list containing "latin1", "cp1252"
    description as "Latin-1 Western European"
    is_ascii_compatible as true
    supports_unicode as false
    byte_order_marks as list containing
    metadata as dictionary containing
    Otherwise:
    Return create_unknown_encoding_info with name as encoding_name

Note: UTF-8 Encoding and Decoding
Process called "encode_utf8" that takes text as String returns EncodingResult:
    Note: Encode Unicode text to UTF-8 bytes
    Try:
    Let encoded_bytes be ""
    Let bytes_processed be 0 For each character in text:
    Let unicode_point be get_unicode_codepoint with char as character
    Let utf8_bytes be codepoint_to_utf8 with codepoint as unicode_point
    Set encoded_bytes to encoded_bytes utf8_bytes
    Set bytes_processed to bytes_processed + 1 Return EncodingResult with:
    success as true
    data as encoded_bytes
    bytes_processed as bytes_processed
    error_message as ""
    encoding_used as "utf-8"
    metadata as dictionary containing Catch error:
    Return EncodingResult with:
    success as false
    data as ""
    bytes_processed as 0
    error_message as "UTF-8 encoding failed"
    encoding_used as "utf-8"
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "decode_utf8" that takes bytes as String returns DecodingResult:
    Note: Decode UTF-8 bytes to Unicode text
    Try:
    Let decoded_text be ""
    Let bytes_consumed be 0
    Let i be 0 While i is less than length of bytes:
    Let utf8_sequence be extract_utf8_sequence with bytes as bytes and start as i
    If utf8_sequence.valid:
    Let unicode_char be utf8_to_character with sequence as utf8_sequence.bytes
    Set decoded_text to decoded_text unicode_char
    Set i to i + utf8_sequence.length
    Set bytes_consumed to bytes_consumed + utf8_sequence.length
    Otherwise:
    Set i to i + 1 Note: Skip invalid byte Return DecodingResult with:
    success as true
    text as decoded_text
    bytes_consumed as bytes_consumed
    error_message as ""
    detected_encoding as "utf-8"
    metadata as dictionary containing Catch error:
    Return DecodingResult with:
    success as false
    text as ""
    bytes_consumed as 0
    error_message as "UTF-8 decoding failed"
    detected_encoding as "utf-8"
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "encode_utf8_with_bom" that takes text as String returns EncodingResult:
    Note: Encode UTF-8 with Byte Order Mark
    Let utf8_result be encode_utf8 with text as text
    If utf8_result.success:
    Return EncodingResult with:
    success as true
    data as utf8_bom utf8_result.data
    bytes_processed as utf8_result.bytes_processed
    error_message as ""
    encoding_used as "utf-8-bom"
    metadata as utf8_result.metadata
    Otherwise:
    Return utf8_result

Note: Base64 Encoding and Decoding
Process called "encode_base64" that takes data as String returns EncodingResult:
    Note: Encode binary data to Base64 string
    Try:
    Let base64_alphabet be "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789+/"
    Let padding_char be "="
    Let result be ""
    Let i be 0 While i is less than length of data:
    Let byte1 be get_byte_value with data as data and index as i
    Let byte2 be 0
    Let byte3 be 0 If i + 1 is less than length of data:
    Set byte2 to get_byte_value with data as data and index as (i + 1)
    If i + 2 is less than length of data:
    Set byte3 to get_byte_value with data as data and index as (i + 2) Let combined be (byte1 multiplied by 65536) + (byte2 multiplied by 256) + byte3 Let char1_index be (combined divided by 262144) mod 64
    Let char2_index be (combined divided by 4096) mod 64
    Let char3_index be (combined divided by 64) mod 64
    Let char4_index be combined mod 64 Set result to result get_base64_char with alphabet as base64_alphabet and index as char1_index
    Set result to result get_base64_char with alphabet as base64_alphabet and index as char2_index If i + 1 is less than length of data:
    Set result to result get_base64_char with alphabet as base64_alphabet and index as char3_index
    Otherwise:
    Set result to result padding_char If i + 2 is less than length of data:
    Set result to result get_base64_char with alphabet as base64_alphabet and index as char4_index
    Otherwise:
    Set result to result padding_char Set i to i + 3 Return EncodingResult with:
    success as true
    data as result
    bytes_processed as length of data
    error_message as ""
    encoding_used as "base64"
    metadata as dictionary containing Catch error:
    Return EncodingResult with:
    success as false
    data as ""
    bytes_processed as 0
    error_message as "Base64 encoding failed"
    encoding_used as "base64"
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "decode_base64" that takes base64_string as String returns DecodingResult:
    Note: Decode Base64 string to binary data
    Try:
    Let base64_alphabet be "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789+/"
    Let padding_char be "="
    Let cleaned_input be remove_base64_whitespace with text as base64_string
    Let result be ""
    Let i be 0 While i is less than length of cleaned_input:
    Let char1 be get_char_at_index with text as cleaned_input and index as i
    Let char2 be get_char_at_index with text as cleaned_input and index as (i + 1)
    Let char3 be get_char_at_index with text as cleaned_input and index as (i + 2)
    Let char4 be get_char_at_index with text as cleaned_input and index as (i + 3) If char1 is equal to padding_char or char2 is equal to padding_char:
    Break Let value1 be get_base64_value with alphabet as base64_alphabet and char as char1
    Let value2 be get_base64_value with alphabet as base64_alphabet and char as char2
    Let value3 be get_base64_value with alphabet as base64_alphabet and char as char3
    Let value4 be get_base64_value with alphabet as base64_alphabet and char as char4 Let combined be (value1 multiplied by 262144) + (value2 multiplied by 4096) + (value3 multiplied by 64) + value4 Let byte1 be (combined divided by 65536) mod 256
    Let byte2 be (combined divided by 256) mod 256
    Let byte3 be combined mod 256 Set result to result character_from_byte with value as byte1 If char3 is not equal to padding_char:
    Set result to result character_from_byte with value as byte2
    If char4 is not equal to padding_char:
    Set result to result character_from_byte with value as byte3 Set i to i + 4 Return DecodingResult with:
    success as true
    text as result
    bytes_consumed as length of cleaned_input
    error_message as ""
    detected_encoding as "base64"
    metadata as dictionary containing Catch error:
    Return DecodingResult with:
    success as false
    text as ""
    bytes_consumed as 0
    error_message as "Base64 decoding failed"
    detected_encoding as "base64"
    metadata as dictionary containing

Note: Hexadecimal Encoding
Process called "encode_hex" that takes data as String returns EncodingResult:
    Note: Encode binary data to hexadecimal string
    Let result be ""
    For each character in data:
    Let byte_value be get_byte_value_from_char with char as character
    Let hex_string be Format.integer_to_hex with value as byte_value
    If length of hex_string is equal to 1:
    Set hex_string to "0" hex_string
    Set result to result hex_string Return EncodingResult with:
    success as true
    data as result
    bytes_processed as length of data
    error_message as ""
    encoding_used as "hex"
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "decode_hex" that takes hex_string as String returns DecodingResult:
    Note: Decode hexadecimal string to binary data
    Let cleaned_hex be Format.lower with s as Format.trim with s as hex_string
    If length of cleaned_hex mod 2 is not equal to 0:
    Return DecodingResult with:
    success as false
    text as ""
    bytes_consumed as 0
    error_message as "Invalid hex string length"
    detected_encoding as "hex"
    metadata as dictionary containing Let result be ""
    Let i be 0 While i is less than length of cleaned_hex:
    Let hex_pair be Format.substring with s as cleaned_hex and start as i and end as (i + 2)
    Let byte_value be hex_string_to_integer with hex as hex_pair
    Let character be character_from_byte with value as byte_value
    Set result to result character
    Set i to i + 2 Return DecodingResult with:
    success as true
    text as result
    bytes_consumed as length of cleaned_hex
    error_message as ""
    detected_encoding as "hex"
    metadata as dictionary containing

Note: URL Encoding and Decoding
Process called "encode_url" that takes text as String returns EncodingResult:
    Note: URL percent-encoding with proper character set handling
    Let result be ""
    Let encoded_count be 0 For each character in text:
    If is_url_safe_char with char as character:
    Set result to result character
    Otherwise:
    Let byte_value be Format.ascii_value_of with char as character
    Let hex_value be Format.integer_to_hex with value as byte_value
    If length of hex_value is equal to 1:
    Set hex_value to "0" hex_value
    Set result to result "%" Format.upper with s as hex_value
    Set encoded_count to encoded_count + 1 Return EncodingResult with:
    success as true
    data as result
    bytes_processed as length of text
    error_message as ""
    encoding_used as "url"
    metadata as dictionary containing "encoded_chars" as encoded_count

Process called "decode_url" that takes url_string as String returns DecodingResult:
    Note: URL percent-decoding with validation
    Let result be ""
    Let i be 0
    Let decoded_count be 0 While i is less than length of url_string:
    Let character be Format.character_at_index with text as url_string and index as i
    If character is equal to "%":
    If i + 2 is less than length of url_string:
    Let hex_string be Format.substring with s as url_string and start as (i + 1) and end as (i + 3)
    If is_valid_hex_string with hex as hex_string:
    Let byte_value be hex_string_to_integer with hex as hex_string
    Let decoded_char be Format.character_from_ascii with value as byte_value
    Set result to result decoded_char
    Set i to i + 3
    Set decoded_count to decoded_count + 1
    Otherwise:
    Set result to result character
    Set i to i + 1
    Otherwise:
    Set result to result character
    Set i to i + 1
    Otherwise if character is equal to "+":
    Set result to result " "
    Set i to i + 1
    Otherwise:
    Set result to result character
    Set i to i + 1 Return DecodingResult with:
    success as true
    text as result
    bytes_consumed as length of url_string
    error_message as ""
    detected_encoding as "url"
    metadata as dictionary containing "decoded_chars" as decoded_count

Note: HTML Entity Encoding and Decoding
Process called "encode_html_entities" that takes text as String returns EncodingResult:
    Note: Encode HTML entities for safe web display
    Let result be ""
    Let entities_encoded be 0 For each character in text:
    Match character:
    When "<":
    Set result to result "&lt;"
    Set entities_encoded to entities_encoded + 1
    When ">":
    Set result to result "&gt;"
    Set entities_encoded to entities_encoded + 1
    When "&":
    Set result to result "&amp;"
    Set entities_encoded to entities_encoded + 1
    When '"':
    Set result to result "&quot;"
    Set entities_encoded to entities_encoded + 1
    When "'":
    Set result to result "&#39;"
    Set entities_encoded to entities_encoded + 1
    Otherwise:
    Set result to result character Return EncodingResult with:
    success as true
    data as result
    bytes_processed as length of text
    error_message as ""
    encoding_used as "html-entities"
    metadata as dictionary containing "entities_encoded" as entities_encoded

Process called "decode_html_entities" that takes html_text as String returns DecodingResult:
    Note: Decode HTML entities to plain text
    Let result be ""
    Let i be 0
    Let entities_decoded be 0 While i is less than length of html_text:
    Let character be Format.character_at_index with text as html_text and index as i
    If character is equal to "&":
    Let entity_end be find_entity_end with text as html_text and start as i
    If entity_end is greater than i:
    Let entity be Format.substring with s as html_text and start as i and end as entity_end + 1
    Let decoded_char be decode_html_entity with entity as entity
    Set result to result decoded_char
    Set i to entity_end + 1
    Set entities_decoded to entities_decoded + 1
    Otherwise:
    Set result to result character
    Set i to i + 1
    Otherwise:
    Set result to result character
    Set i to i + 1 Return DecodingResult with:
    success as true
    text as result
    bytes_consumed as length of html_text
    error_message as ""
    detected_encoding as "html-entities"
    metadata as dictionary containing "entities_decoded" as entities_decoded

Note: Unicode Normalization and Processing
Process called "normalize_unicode" that takes text as String and form as String returns String:
    Note: Normalize Unicode text according to specified form (NFC, NFD, NFKC, NFKD)
    Match form:
    When "NFC":
    Return normalize_composed with text as text and compatible as false
    When "NFD":
    Return normalize_decomposed with text as text and compatible as false
    When "NFKC":
    Return normalize_composed with text as text and compatible as true
    When "NFKD":
    Return normalize_decomposed with text as text and compatible as true
    Otherwise:
    Return text

Process called "case_fold_unicode" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Unicode case folding for case-insensitive comparison
    Let result be ""
    For each character in text:
    Let folded_char be get_case_folded_char with char as character
    Set result to result folded_char Return result

Process called "get_unicode_category" that takes character as String returns String:
    Note: Get Unicode general category for character
    Let codepoint be get_unicode_codepoint with char as character
    Return get_category_for_codepoint with codepoint as codepoint

Note: Utility Functions for Encoding Operations
Process called "get_unicode_codepoint" that takes char as String returns Integer:
    Note: Get Unicode codepoint for character
    Note: Basic implementation - would use Unicode tables in production
    Return Format.ascii_value_of with char as char

Process called "codepoint_to_utf8" that takes codepoint as Integer returns String:
    Note: Convert Unicode codepoint to UTF-8 byte sequence
    If codepoint is less than or equal to 127:
    Return Format.character_from_ascii with value as codepoint
    Otherwise if codepoint is less than or equal to 2047:
    Let byte1 be 192 + (codepoint divided by 64)
    Let byte2 be 128 + (codepoint mod 64)
    Return character_from_byte with value as byte1 character_from_byte with value as byte2
    Otherwise if codepoint is less than or equal to 65535:
    Let byte1 be 224 + (codepoint divided by 4096)
    Let byte2 be 128 + ((codepoint divided by 64) mod 64)
    Let byte3 be 128 + (codepoint mod 64)
    Return character_from_byte with value as byte1 character_from_byte with value as byte2 character_from_byte with value as byte3
    Otherwise:
    Let byte1 be 240 + (codepoint divided by 262144)
    Let byte2 be 128 + ((codepoint divided by 4096) mod 64)
    Let byte3 be 128 + ((codepoint divided by 64) mod 64)
    Let byte4 be 128 + (codepoint mod 64)
    Return character_from_byte with value as byte1 character_from_byte with value as byte2 character_from_byte with value as byte3 character_from_byte with value as byte4

Process called "character_from_byte" that takes value as Integer returns String:
    Note: Convert byte value to character
    If value is greater than or equal to 0 and value is less than or equal to 255:
    Return Format.character_from_ascii with value as value
    Otherwise:
    Return ""

Process called "get_byte_value_from_char" that takes char as String returns Integer:
    Note: Get byte value from character
    Return Format.ascii_value_of with char as char

Process called "hex_string_to_integer" that takes hex as String returns Integer:
    Note: Convert hexadecimal string to integer
    Let result be 0
    Let power be 1 For i from (length of hex - 1) down to 0:
    Let hex_char be Format.character_at_index with text as hex and index as i
    Let digit_value be hex_char_to_value with char as hex_char
    Set result to result + (digit_value multiplied by power)
    Set power to power multiplied by 16 Return result

Process called "hex_char_to_value" that takes char as String returns Integer:
    Note: Convert hex character to numeric value
    Match char:
    When "0": Return 0
    When "1": Return 1
    When "2": Return 2
    When "3": Return 3
    When "4": Return 4
    When "5": Return 5
    When "6": Return 6
    When "7": Return 7
    When "8": Return 8
    When "9": Return 9
    When "a": Return 10
    When "b": Return 11
    When "c": Return 12
    When "d": Return 13
    When "e": Return 14
    When "f": Return 15
    When "A": Return 10
    When "B": Return 11
    When "C": Return 12
    When "D": Return 13
    When "E": Return 14
    When "F": Return 15
    Otherwise: Return 0

Process called "is_valid_hex_string" that takes hex as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Validate hexadecimal string format
    If length of hex is equal to 0:
    Return false For each character in hex:
    If not is_hex_char with char as character:
    Return false Return true

Process called "is_hex_char" that takes char as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if character is valid hexadecimal digit
    Return (char is greater than or equal to "0" and char is less than or equal to "9") or 
    (char is greater than or equal to "a" and char is less than or equal to "f") or
    (char is greater than or equal to "A" and char is less than or equal to "F")

Process called "is_url_safe_char" that takes char as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if character is URL-safe (doesn't need encoding)
    Return (char is greater than or equal to "A" and char is less than or equal to "Z") or
    (char is greater than or equal to "a" and char is less than or equal to "z") or
    (char is greater than or equal to "0" and char is less than or equal to "9") or
    char is equal to "-" or char is equal to "_" or char is equal to "." or char is equal to "~"

Note: Encoding Constants and BOMs
Process called "get_utf8_bom" returns String:
    Note: UTF-8 Byte Order Mark
    Return "\xEF\xBB\xBF"

Process called "get_utf16_be_bom" returns String:
    Note: UTF-16 Big Endian BOM
    Return "\xFE\xFF"

Process called "get_utf16_le_bom" returns String:
    Note: UTF-16 Little Endian BOM
    Return "\xFF\xFE"

Process called "get_utf32_be_bom" returns String:
    Note: UTF-32 Big Endian BOM
    Return "\x00\x00\xFE\xFF"

Process called "get_utf32_le_bom" returns String:
    Note: UTF-32 Little Endian BOM
    Return "\xFF\xFE\x00\x00"

Let utf8_bom be get_utf8_bom
Let utf16_be_bom be get_utf16_be_bom
Let utf16_le_bom be get_utf16_le_bom
Let utf32_be_bom be get_utf32_be_bom
Let utf32_le_bom be get_utf32_le_bom

Note: Additional Utility Functions
Process called "starts_with_bom" that takes data as String and bom as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if data starts with specified BOM
    If length of data is less than length of bom:
    Return false Let prefix be Format.substring with s as data and start as 0 and end as length of bom
    Return prefix is equal to bom

Process called "remove_base64_whitespace" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Remove whitespace characters from Base64 string
    Let result be ""
    For each character in text:
    If not Format.is_whitespace_char with char as character:
    Set result to result character
    Return result

Process called "get_base64_char" that takes alphabet as String and index as Integer returns String:
    Note: Get Base64 character at index
    If index is greater than or equal to 0 and index is less than length of alphabet:
    Return Format.character_at_index with text as alphabet and index as index
    Otherwise:
    Return ""

Process called "get_base64_value" that takes alphabet as String and char as String returns Integer:
    Note: Get numeric value for Base64 character
    For i from 0 to (length of alphabet - 1):
    Let alphabet_char be Format.character_at_index with text as alphabet and index as i
    If alphabet_char is equal to char:
    Return i
    Return 0

Process called "decode_html_entity" that takes entity as String returns String:
    Note: Decode single HTML entity to character
    Match entity:
    When "&lt;": Return "<"
    When "&gt;": Return ">"
    When "&amp;": Return "&"
    When "&quot;": Return '"'
    When "&#39;": Return "'"
    When "&nbsp;": Return " "
    Otherwise: Return entity

Process called "find_entity_end" that takes text as String and start as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Find the end of HTML entity starting at position
    For i from (start + 1) to (length of text - 1):
    Let char be Format.character_at_index with text as text and index as i
    If char is equal to ";":
    Return i
    Otherwise if char is equal to " " or char is equal to "&":
    Return start Note: Invalid entity
    Return start Note: No terminator found

Process called "get_char_at_index" that takes text as String and index as Integer returns String:
    Note: Safe character access with bounds checking
    If index is less than 0 or index is greater than or equal to length of text:
    Return ""
    Return Format.character_at_index with text as text and index as index

Process called "create_unknown_encoding_info" that takes name as String returns CharacterSetInfo:
    Note: Create info structure for unknown encoding
    Return CharacterSetInfo with:
    name as name
    aliases as list containing
    description as "Unknown encoding"
    is_ascii_compatible as false
    supports_unicode as false
    byte_order_marks as list containing
    metadata as dictionary containing "unknown" as true

Note: Encoding Validation Functions
Process called "validate_ascii" that takes text as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Validate that text contains only ASCII characters (0-127)
    For each character in text:
    Let char_code be Format.ascii_value_of with char as character
    If char_code is less than 0 or char_code is greater than 127:
    Return false
    Return true

Process called "validate_utf8" that takes text as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Validate UTF-8 encoding - basic implementation
    Try:
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than length of text:
    Let byte1 be get_byte_value_from_char with char as Format.character_at_index with text as text and index as i If byte1 is less than or equal to 127:
    Note: Single byte UTF-8 character
    Set i to i + 1
    Otherwise if byte1 is greater than or equal to 194 and byte1 is less than or equal to 223:
    Note: Two byte UTF-8 character
    If i + 1 is greater than or equal to length of text:
    Return false
    Let byte2 be get_byte_value_from_char with char as Format.character_at_index with text as text and index as (i + 1)
    If byte2 is less than 128 or byte2 is greater than 191:
    Return false
    Set i to i + 2
    Otherwise if byte1 is greater than or equal to 224 and byte1 is less than or equal to 239:
    Note: Three byte UTF-8 character
    If i + 2 is greater than or equal to length of text:
    Return false
    Set i to i + 3
    Otherwise if byte1 is greater than or equal to 240 and byte1 is less than or equal to 244:
    Note: Four byte UTF-8 character
    If i + 3 is greater than or equal to length of text:
    Return false
    Set i to i + 4
    Otherwise:
    Return false
    Return true Catch error:
    Return false

